End-to-End Platform Flow
STEP 1 — ONBOARDING
│
├── Worker visits GigShield PWA (via WhatsApp link / QR code)
├── Phone number entered → OTP verified
├── Platform ID linked (Swiggy/Zomato partner ID)
├── Operating zone selected (pincode / GPS polygon)
├── Average weekly earning declared
└── UPI ID / bank account added for payouts
│
▼
STEP 2 — AI RISK PROFILING
│
├── ML model runs on worker profile:
│   ├── Zone's historical disruption frequency
│   ├── Current season / month (monsoon vs dry)
│   ├── Historical working hours pattern
│   └── Platform activity score (simulated API)
└── Risk score generated (0.8 – 2.0 multiplier)
│
▼
STEP 3 — POLICY CREATION
│
├── Worker sees AI-recommended coverage tier
├── Three tiers displayed with weekly premium and max payout
├── Worker selects tier and confirms
└── Weekly UPI AutoPay mandate set up via Razorpay
│
▼
STEP 4 — REAL-TIME TRIGGER MONITORING (Background — every 15 min)
│
├── Weather API polled → Rain / Heat / Flood thresholds checked
├── AQI API polled → Pollution severity checked per zone
├── News + Traffic API polled → Bandh / curfew signals detected
└── Platform API (mock) → Order volume drop signals
│
▼
STEP 5 — AUTOMATIC CLAIM INITIATION (On threshold breach)
│
├── Fraud Layer 1: Is worker's GPS inside the disrupted zone polygon?
├── Fraud Layer 2: Was worker active on platform 2 hours before event?
├── Fraud Layer 3: Cross-validate with IMD station + peer claim rate
└── Decision: AUTO APPROVE | FLAG FOR REVIEW | AUTO REJECT
│
▼
STEP 6 — PAYOUT PROCESSING
│
├── Payout = Affected Hours × Avg Hourly Rate × Coverage Percentage
├── Capped at policy tier's maximum daily payout
├── Transferred via UPI / Razorpay sandbox
└── Worker notified via SMS + in-app push notification
│
▼
STEP 7 — DASHBOARD UPDATE
│
├── Worker view: Claim logged, payout shown, earnings protected updated
└── Insurer view: Claim event recorded, loss ratio recalculated, fraud flags updated

